1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,572 --> 00:01:08,698
EPISODE 13

3
00:01:13,661 --> 00:01:15,997
This is our house. Come on in.

4
00:01:45,819 --> 00:01:48,279
Okay. This is my secret room.

5
00:01:53,868 --> 00:01:57,205
When I open this handle
and press this button…

6
00:02:25,775 --> 00:02:27,861
Okay. What do you think?

7
00:02:37,912 --> 00:02:39,581
It's empty.

8
00:02:40,832 --> 00:02:41,833
Look here.

9
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:43,877
It looks like something has been moved.

10
00:02:44,794 --> 00:02:46,296
The marks look fresh.

11
00:02:47,338 --> 00:02:48,923
Gosh, my dear father.

12
00:02:49,007 --> 00:02:53,636
He must've secretly stashed it here,
but I guess that bitch got to it again.

13
00:02:55,722 --> 00:02:59,726
He didn't even tell
his own children about this secret room.

14
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,670
Did you send him off well?

15
00:03:27,754 --> 00:03:31,132
It was you, wasn't it?
You killed our father.

16
00:03:31,216 --> 00:03:32,926
-Why would I?
-Because you didn't need him

17
00:03:33,009 --> 00:03:35,220
after taking his money.

18
00:03:35,303 --> 00:03:36,763
Where is it?

19
00:03:36,846 --> 00:03:38,890
I don't know what you're saying.

20
00:03:38,973 --> 00:03:41,142
Your father is dead,
and you still want his money.

21
00:03:41,226 --> 00:03:44,020
-Your poor father.
-Cut the nonsense.

22
00:03:45,230 --> 00:03:46,981
Leave this house right now.

23
00:03:47,065 --> 00:03:49,067
You have no right to be here anymore.

24
00:03:49,984 --> 00:03:52,111
I'm a legal resident here.

25
00:03:52,195 --> 00:03:55,573
If you want to kick me out,
the court needs to order it first.

26
00:03:56,532 --> 00:03:58,284
Aren't you aware of this, Attorney Baek?

27
00:03:58,368 --> 00:04:00,411
Is this true? We can't just kick her out?

28
00:04:00,495 --> 00:04:03,456
There's a procedure,
but you'll have to leave.

29
00:04:03,539 --> 00:04:05,166
We'll see about that.

30
00:04:06,668 --> 00:04:08,419
We're moving back in.

31
00:04:08,503 --> 00:04:10,421
-Do you still want to stay?
-Why not?

32
00:04:10,505 --> 00:04:12,382
We've been living together
for over 20 years.

33
00:04:12,465 --> 00:04:13,716
You said we were family.

34
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,176
-But--
-Suit yourself.

35
00:04:16,135 --> 00:04:17,887
We'll be back soon.

36
00:04:17,971 --> 00:04:19,347
Let's see if you can bear it.

37
00:04:52,797 --> 00:04:53,756
Hae-in.

38
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,096
Grandfather?

39
00:05:00,763 --> 00:05:03,683
I would've loved to speak to you

40
00:05:03,766 --> 00:05:05,184
in person.

41
00:05:06,686 --> 00:05:07,520
But still,

42
00:05:08,146 --> 00:05:11,816
I'm glad I can talk to you like this.

43
00:05:13,026 --> 00:05:14,027
Thank you.

44
00:05:19,907 --> 00:05:23,661
I briefly come to my senses
every now and then

45
00:05:23,745 --> 00:05:27,498
like a basement
that receives limited sunlight.

46
00:05:28,207 --> 00:05:32,045
But there's not much I can do.

47
00:05:33,254 --> 00:05:35,131
I don't remember much either.

48
00:05:35,214 --> 00:05:38,009
I'm just full of regrets.

49
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:41,846
I've been a money-grubber all my life.

50
00:05:41,929 --> 00:05:43,806
I did everything in my power

51
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:47,060
to keep the money I gathered.

52
00:05:47,685 --> 00:05:51,564
I wasted most of my years doing that.

53
00:05:54,776 --> 00:05:56,944
What am I left with?

54
00:05:57,987 --> 00:06:02,283
I'd like you all to know that I regret

55
00:06:03,034 --> 00:06:05,828
the life I led.

56
00:06:05,912 --> 00:06:07,455
FORMER CHAIRMAN HONG MAN-DAE

57
00:06:07,538 --> 00:06:11,376
I hope you live differently.

58
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:13,836
I truly hope

59
00:06:14,879 --> 00:06:18,257
that you won't look back in futility

60
00:06:18,341 --> 00:06:20,218
at the end of the road.

61
00:06:37,568 --> 00:06:39,237
Dad…

62
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:45,660
Dad…

63
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:12,895
I love you all.

64
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:14,814
And…

65
00:07:17,608 --> 00:07:18,776
I'm sorry.

66
00:07:28,995 --> 00:07:31,581
You need to eat even if you're not hungry.

67
00:07:53,144 --> 00:07:55,563
Do you want to go
inside the car if you're cold?

68
00:07:55,646 --> 00:07:56,481
It's okay.

69
00:08:05,531 --> 00:08:06,699
This feels

70
00:08:07,450 --> 00:08:08,743
very strange.

71
00:08:09,952 --> 00:08:12,622
It feels like I'm doing a rehearsal.

72
00:08:13,581 --> 00:08:14,582
A rehearsal?

73
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:16,209
A death rehearsal.

74
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,801
I didn't know

75
00:08:26,761 --> 00:08:28,137
a funeral was so complex.

76
00:08:29,055 --> 00:08:32,725
They dig a hole in the ground,
place the coffin,

77
00:08:32,808 --> 00:08:36,687
have some rice soup in a tent,
and mourn by the grave.

78
00:08:37,605 --> 00:08:38,814
Then when it's time,

79
00:08:39,690 --> 00:08:41,984
they'll all go home.

80
00:08:44,612 --> 00:08:45,988
And I'll be all by myself.

81
00:08:51,118 --> 00:08:54,413
You know that the three months
I've been given

82
00:08:55,164 --> 00:08:56,165
have already passed.

83
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:02,505
I could even die tonight.

84
00:09:03,506 --> 00:09:06,300
But my family
would have to mourn again if I died.

85
00:09:07,218 --> 00:09:08,052
That wouldn't

86
00:09:08,761 --> 00:09:10,638
look good for our family, right?

87
00:09:11,639 --> 00:09:12,473
Was that

88
00:09:14,392 --> 00:09:15,810
what you've been worrying about?

89
00:09:16,561 --> 00:09:18,521
That your family would mourn again?

90
00:09:20,356 --> 00:09:21,190
No.

91
00:09:25,027 --> 00:09:27,196
I kept thinking that I wanted to live.

92
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:38,708
It's sunny.

93
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,211
The clouds look pretty,
and the birds are chirping.

94
00:09:44,171 --> 00:09:47,174
This world is annoyingly beautiful.

95
00:09:51,846 --> 00:09:53,389
So, of course, I want to live.

96
00:11:15,971 --> 00:11:17,264
CHECKING ID
PLEASE WAIT

97
00:11:39,370 --> 00:11:40,913
How did you find it?

98
00:11:42,915 --> 00:11:44,250
DREAMLAND THEME PARK

99
00:12:02,143 --> 00:12:04,854
Okay. This is my secret room.

100
00:12:09,358 --> 00:12:12,570
When I open this handle
and press this button…

101
00:12:19,201 --> 00:12:20,202
Thank you.

102
00:12:23,581 --> 00:12:24,623
I told you.

103
00:12:25,124 --> 00:12:27,209
I loved you in my own way.

104
00:12:33,632 --> 00:12:35,342
This money will keep you safe.

105
00:12:44,226 --> 00:12:46,187
His daughter is sick,

106
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:47,813
and now, he lost his father.

107
00:12:47,897 --> 00:12:51,400
Mr. Hong must be devastated.

108
00:12:52,485 --> 00:12:53,402
Right.

109
00:12:53,486 --> 00:12:56,822
But you can say
things are looking up for his family

110
00:12:56,906 --> 00:12:58,908
after the chairman passed away.

111
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:00,951
-Is that so?
-Gosh.

112
00:13:02,203 --> 00:13:03,537
Hear me out.

113
00:13:04,622 --> 00:13:05,664
Look.

114
00:13:05,748 --> 00:13:07,666
Chairman Hong had entrusted
21% of his shares

115
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:10,753
to that woman, Moh Seul-hee.

116
00:13:10,836 --> 00:13:12,463
But now that he's passed away,

117
00:13:12,546 --> 00:13:15,424
-his family received it.
-I see.

118
00:13:15,508 --> 00:13:19,553
Yoon Eun-sung's total shares were 59.1%.

119
00:13:19,637 --> 00:13:22,556
But now, it has plummeted to 38.1%.

120
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:26,227
Once our in-laws get hold
of their frozen shares,

121
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:29,313
-they'll have 34.7% in total.
-I see.

122
00:13:29,396 --> 00:13:31,941
Then the gap will be 3.4%.

123
00:13:32,024 --> 00:13:33,776
-That's quite neck and neck.
-Right.

124
00:13:33,859 --> 00:13:35,611
How do you know this so well?

125
00:13:35,694 --> 00:13:37,279
-I'm a club member.
-What club?

126
00:13:37,363 --> 00:13:38,823
The Queens Minor Stockholders' Club.

127
00:13:38,906 --> 00:13:44,286
We're waiting for the management
feud results with bated breath.

128
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:47,331
What for?

129
00:13:47,414 --> 00:13:50,376
I know I'm being calculating.

130
00:13:50,459 --> 00:13:51,585
But what do you think

131
00:13:51,669 --> 00:13:53,420
-will happen to Hyun-woo?
-What do you mean?

132
00:13:53,504 --> 00:13:55,339
Let's be honest. He's been doing

133
00:13:55,422 --> 00:13:58,843
his utmost best to help them
after everything.

134
00:13:58,926 --> 00:14:00,719
Perhaps, they'll thank him in some way.

135
00:14:00,803 --> 00:14:05,474
Maybe they'll give him some shares
or appoint him as a CEO later on.

136
00:14:07,226 --> 00:14:08,394
I don't ask for much,

137
00:14:09,061 --> 00:14:12,481
but could you do me this one favor?

138
00:14:13,065 --> 00:14:14,483
Sure.

139
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:15,401
What is it?

140
00:14:16,151 --> 00:14:18,863
If someone asks you who your father is,

141
00:14:18,946 --> 00:14:21,282
please don't tell them it's me.

142
00:14:22,324 --> 00:14:23,450
Jeez.

143
00:14:23,534 --> 00:14:24,785
Why not?

144
00:14:25,536 --> 00:14:27,621
Why not? Hey, wait for me.

145
00:14:36,964 --> 00:14:38,549
Thank you for everything.

146
00:14:38,632 --> 00:14:40,801
Gosh, don't mention it.

147
00:14:42,386 --> 00:14:45,723
Things will look up
once you return to Seoul.

148
00:14:46,599 --> 00:14:47,808
Do you think so?

149
00:14:59,528 --> 00:15:00,362
You see…

150
00:15:01,572 --> 00:15:04,325
These persimmons

151
00:15:04,408 --> 00:15:06,744
used to be very bitter.

152
00:15:06,827 --> 00:15:10,623
But there's a way
to turn this awfully bitter fruit

153
00:15:10,706 --> 00:15:12,041
-into a sweet one.
-How?

154
00:15:12,124 --> 00:15:14,043
It's by soaking them.

155
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,713
You pour some soju on top,

156
00:15:17,796 --> 00:15:21,508
wrap the bodies,
then let them sit for some time.

157
00:15:21,592 --> 00:15:23,093
Then they become sweet.

158
00:15:25,471 --> 00:15:27,514
Here. Try it.

159
00:15:33,187 --> 00:15:34,313
It's sweet.

160
00:15:36,732 --> 00:15:40,819
Life can be bitter
just like these persimmons.

161
00:15:42,738 --> 00:15:44,156
Life is tough as is,

162
00:15:44,239 --> 00:15:46,533
so imagine pouring
some bitter soju on top.

163
00:15:46,617 --> 00:15:49,370
Gosh, it'd be utterly unbearable.

164
00:15:49,453 --> 00:15:51,455
But if you endure it,

165
00:15:51,538 --> 00:15:53,916
life will become sweet again.

166
00:15:53,999 --> 00:15:55,918
And that'll motivate you to stay strong.

167
00:15:56,001 --> 00:15:57,294
Don't you think so?

168
00:15:59,797 --> 00:16:01,006
Right.

169
00:16:02,758 --> 00:16:05,094
Hey, come and have a drink with us.

170
00:16:05,177 --> 00:16:06,387
Sure.

171
00:16:09,431 --> 00:16:10,432
INTERNATIONAL CALL

172
00:16:10,516 --> 00:16:13,268
I got a call from Germany. Excuse me.

173
00:16:44,341 --> 00:16:47,428
Does that mean she can receive surgery?

174
00:16:48,095 --> 00:16:49,096
Yes.

175
00:16:50,639 --> 00:16:51,640
Thank God.

176
00:16:51,724 --> 00:16:56,812
Her case was a difficult one
since they couldn't open up her brain.

177
00:16:56,895 --> 00:16:59,982
But they can destroy the tumor cells

178
00:17:00,649 --> 00:17:02,735
using high-intensity ultrasound.

179
00:17:02,818 --> 00:17:04,653
They had a successful case recently too.

180
00:17:04,737 --> 00:17:06,697
Good. Things are looking up now.

181
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:09,158
Thanks, Hyun-woo. Does Hae-in know?

182
00:17:09,241 --> 00:17:10,743
-I should tell her.
-However…

183
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:13,120
there's a problem.

184
00:17:16,123 --> 00:17:19,501
Goodness, Hae-in. This feels like a dream.

185
00:17:19,585 --> 00:17:22,004
Gosh, this must be a gift

186
00:17:22,087 --> 00:17:23,839
from Father.

187
00:17:23,922 --> 00:17:24,757
Is it true?

188
00:17:25,632 --> 00:17:27,593
-Can she receive surgery?
-Yes.

189
00:17:29,803 --> 00:17:30,971
I'm so happy for you.

190
00:17:31,055 --> 00:17:32,222
Goodness.

191
00:17:32,306 --> 00:17:34,516
I'm so grateful.

192
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,143
Congratulations.

193
00:17:36,226 --> 00:17:38,103
Congratulations, sweetie.

194
00:18:38,747 --> 00:18:40,791
How did they reach you? Via email? Phone?

195
00:18:40,874 --> 00:18:42,042
Was it a video call?

196
00:18:42,126 --> 00:18:43,210
They called me.

197
00:18:43,293 --> 00:18:44,128
A phone call?

198
00:18:45,838 --> 00:18:49,091
You don't think
they were scammers, do you?

199
00:18:49,174 --> 00:18:50,008
No, they weren't.

200
00:18:50,092 --> 00:18:51,009
I see.

201
00:18:51,802 --> 00:18:52,803
Okay. Good night.

202
00:18:54,721 --> 00:18:59,268
By the way, are you sure
the surgery works in rare cases like mine?

203
00:18:59,351 --> 00:19:00,394
Yes.

204
00:19:00,894 --> 00:19:01,895
I'm sure.

205
00:19:01,979 --> 00:19:02,980
I see.

206
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:07,401
And the date?

207
00:19:07,484 --> 00:19:08,986
Tell them I can go right away.

208
00:19:09,069 --> 00:19:10,112
I did.

209
00:19:11,238 --> 00:19:12,239
Good then.

210
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:23,667
Are you saying

211
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,003
that this surgery

212
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:29,298
will save my life?

213
00:19:31,967 --> 00:19:33,302
Does Hae-in know?

214
00:19:33,385 --> 00:19:34,803
I should tell her.

215
00:19:34,887 --> 00:19:35,721
However…

216
00:19:36,930 --> 00:19:38,098
there's a problem.

217
00:19:38,182 --> 00:19:40,434
A part of the hippocampus will be damaged

218
00:19:40,517 --> 00:19:42,936
-during the process.
-And?

219
00:19:44,688 --> 00:19:45,981
It's highly likely…

220
00:19:48,150 --> 00:19:50,152
that she'll lose her long-term memory.

221
00:19:52,446 --> 00:19:53,488
Hold on.

222
00:19:54,239 --> 00:19:55,991
What are you saying?

223
00:19:56,074 --> 00:19:57,868
She could lose all her memory

224
00:19:59,328 --> 00:20:00,787
from before the surgery.

225
00:20:08,503 --> 00:20:09,838
But this is our only choice

226
00:20:10,464 --> 00:20:11,590
if we want her

227
00:20:12,216 --> 00:20:13,508
to live.

228
00:20:14,092 --> 00:20:16,178
Her WBC isn't going up quickly,

229
00:20:16,261 --> 00:20:18,597
so she can't receive the clinical test.

230
00:20:19,556 --> 00:20:20,933
We really have no time now.

231
00:20:21,016 --> 00:20:23,727
She might refuse the surgery

232
00:20:24,519 --> 00:20:27,022
if she hears about the side effects.

233
00:20:27,648 --> 00:20:28,565
But what if

234
00:20:29,942 --> 00:20:32,569
she runs out of time?

235
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,488
Hyun-woo.

236
00:20:35,072 --> 00:20:36,823
Keep this a secret.

237
00:20:36,907 --> 00:20:41,411
Why don't you take her to Germany first,
then persuade her there?

238
00:20:42,663 --> 00:20:43,789
I beg you.

239
00:20:44,498 --> 00:20:48,126
She needs the surgery to live.

240
00:20:48,752 --> 00:20:50,379
Will I be able to live then?

241
00:20:53,257 --> 00:20:54,424
What is it?

242
00:20:57,511 --> 00:20:58,512
Yes, you will.

243
00:21:00,013 --> 00:21:01,223
Don't worry.

244
00:21:07,062 --> 00:21:08,063
All right.

245
00:21:09,648 --> 00:21:10,649
Night.

246
00:21:41,972 --> 00:21:43,098
Hae-in.

247
00:21:59,781 --> 00:22:00,866
It's okay.

248
00:22:01,616 --> 00:22:03,618
I'm fine. I really am.

249
00:22:04,453 --> 00:22:07,247
It's just been ages since I felt fine.

250
00:22:07,331 --> 00:22:10,083
These are tears of joy.

251
00:22:13,503 --> 00:22:14,629
Yes, I know.

252
00:22:19,051 --> 00:22:20,302
It feels like

253
00:22:21,928 --> 00:22:24,056
I woke up from a long nightmare.

254
00:22:38,153 --> 00:22:39,321
You're okay now.

255
00:23:07,557 --> 00:23:08,934
Let's go to bed.

256
00:24:14,332 --> 00:24:17,919
HAE-IN
HYUN-WOO

257
00:24:55,248 --> 00:24:57,083
You don't have to go to work today, right?

258
00:25:00,128 --> 00:25:00,962
No.

259
00:25:02,214 --> 00:25:03,340
Then let's hang out.

260
00:25:07,928 --> 00:25:08,929
Okay, let's do that.

261
00:25:14,017 --> 00:25:17,229
GURANG-RI STATION

262
00:25:23,693 --> 00:25:25,320
TICKET OFFICE

263
00:25:25,946 --> 00:25:26,780
Two people.

264
00:25:29,199 --> 00:25:30,242
All right.

265
00:25:56,476 --> 00:25:58,687
-Okay, good.
-What?

266
00:26:19,833 --> 00:26:22,794
Other than our honeymoon,
isn't this our first trip?

267
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:24,754
You're right.

268
00:26:24,838 --> 00:26:26,965
I've been too much of a workaholic.

269
00:26:27,632 --> 00:26:30,802
Let's go on many trips
after I receive surgery.

270
00:26:31,886 --> 00:26:33,096
Promise.

271
00:26:35,432 --> 00:26:36,600
Okay.

272
00:27:06,504 --> 00:27:07,422
Listen.

273
00:27:07,505 --> 00:27:10,467
I want everything to be smooth
before I receive surgery.

274
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:14,429
You know I only drink extracted juice
for the same reason, right?

275
00:27:15,555 --> 00:27:17,641
I do. What's on your mind?

276
00:27:18,767 --> 00:27:20,810
I wasn't planning on hiding them,

277
00:27:20,894 --> 00:27:22,937
but there are three things
I kept from you.

278
00:27:23,021 --> 00:27:24,064
Three?

279
00:27:24,147 --> 00:27:26,232
I'll come clean before I go.

280
00:27:26,316 --> 00:27:27,984
I'll tell you one for today.

281
00:27:29,486 --> 00:27:30,487
Sure. What is it?

282
00:27:31,154 --> 00:27:32,155
You said

283
00:27:33,448 --> 00:27:35,533
that you found this MP3.

284
00:27:36,117 --> 00:27:36,951
I did.

285
00:27:37,952 --> 00:27:39,079
It's mine.

286
00:27:39,829 --> 00:27:42,624
-What?
-Do you see this "H"?

287
00:27:42,707 --> 00:27:44,167
It stands for "Hae-in".

288
00:27:44,250 --> 00:27:48,505
I had lost it in our schoolyard
before going abroad for my studies.

289
00:27:48,588 --> 00:27:50,173
And look where it is now.

290
00:27:55,637 --> 00:27:56,471
That can't be.

291
00:27:56,554 --> 00:27:58,306
It sure can.

292
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,648
I don't believe it.

293
00:28:06,731 --> 00:28:09,651
Something unbelievable happened to us.

294
00:28:12,237 --> 00:28:14,072
It may not mean much to you

295
00:28:14,155 --> 00:28:17,283
since I was just a nobody in your life.

296
00:28:18,159 --> 00:28:19,744
No, you're wrong.

297
00:28:20,995 --> 00:28:22,539
Listen. I actually--

298
00:28:23,289 --> 00:28:24,499
Don't be afraid.

299
00:28:24,582 --> 00:28:26,167
I'm not scolding you. Why?

300
00:28:26,251 --> 00:28:28,294
Because I'm not the old me.

301
00:28:29,587 --> 00:28:30,964
I'll be reborn soon.

302
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:36,636
I'm going to be optimistic

303
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:38,179
and only see the good in life.

304
00:28:41,641 --> 00:28:42,767
Is that so?

305
00:28:42,851 --> 00:28:43,685
Yes.

306
00:28:43,768 --> 00:28:46,479
This MP3
is a living witness to our history.

307
00:28:46,563 --> 00:28:49,858
So I'm only going to focus
on that positive point.

308
00:28:55,155 --> 00:28:55,989
That's good.

309
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,908
Eun-sung told me

310
00:28:58,992 --> 00:29:01,077
how he had saved me in the past

311
00:29:01,161 --> 00:29:03,580
and made it seem like we were fated.

312
00:29:03,663 --> 00:29:05,081
What? Fated?

313
00:29:05,957 --> 00:29:06,875
Jeez.

314
00:29:06,958 --> 00:29:09,669
Has he gone crazy or what?
How dare he say that?

315
00:29:09,753 --> 00:29:13,423
So what? We have our own movie-like story.

316
00:29:14,132 --> 00:29:16,134
When I saw you at the schoolyard,

317
00:29:22,557 --> 00:29:25,018
I thought, "Does this handsome kid
go to my school?

318
00:29:26,060 --> 00:29:27,854
I can't believe I'm leaving.

319
00:29:28,646 --> 00:29:29,981
I feel terrible."

320
00:29:30,064 --> 00:29:31,608
That's what I thought.

321
00:29:32,942 --> 00:29:34,360
Black slip-ons.

322
00:29:35,612 --> 00:29:36,613
You were wearing

323
00:29:38,114 --> 00:29:39,407
black slip-ons.

324
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:41,826
You had white socks

325
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:44,454
and very fair skin.

326
00:29:45,580 --> 00:29:49,334
And your hair was in a high ponytail.

327
00:29:50,168 --> 00:29:53,129
I did wear ponytails often back then.

328
00:29:53,213 --> 00:29:55,006
The moment I saw you, I thought,

329
00:29:55,882 --> 00:29:56,883
"I found her."

330
00:29:57,592 --> 00:29:58,718
"My dream girl."

331
00:30:01,179 --> 00:30:03,848
I looked everywhere for you
starting the next day.

332
00:30:04,849 --> 00:30:07,393
I didn't have a chance
to look at your name tag.

333
00:30:08,186 --> 00:30:09,854
-Really?
-Yeah.

334
00:30:09,938 --> 00:30:11,731
You were like Cinderella.

335
00:30:11,815 --> 00:30:14,108
You had only left behind your MP3.

336
00:30:14,192 --> 00:30:15,109
It drove me crazy.

337
00:30:16,194 --> 00:30:17,487
But look at us now.

338
00:30:17,570 --> 00:30:20,406
We crossed paths again, got married…

339
00:30:21,616 --> 00:30:24,285
We did get divorced, but still.

340
00:30:24,953 --> 00:30:28,957
This is what you call true fate.

341
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:29,874
All right.

342
00:30:30,625 --> 00:30:33,503
Since I'm your dream woman,

343
00:30:33,586 --> 00:30:35,255
and this is fate…

344
00:30:35,338 --> 00:30:36,339
From now on…

345
00:30:42,178 --> 00:30:43,179
I didn't know

346
00:30:45,265 --> 00:30:47,141
that phrase was this beautiful.

347
00:30:51,229 --> 00:30:52,522
I'm getting teary-eyed.

348
00:30:59,404 --> 00:31:02,365
I thought I wouldn't be
a part of your future.

349
00:31:03,700 --> 00:31:05,243
But now, we have a future together.

350
00:31:14,294 --> 00:31:15,295
Speaking of which…

351
00:31:24,304 --> 00:31:26,222
I'll withdraw our divorce like you asked.

352
00:31:36,065 --> 00:31:37,400
What's with that face?

353
00:31:48,202 --> 00:31:49,203
Don't take it back.

354
00:31:49,913 --> 00:31:51,205
I run a department store.

355
00:31:51,289 --> 00:31:54,959
I hate customers
who return things and demand a refund.

356
00:31:57,462 --> 00:31:59,339
You can't take this back

357
00:32:00,590 --> 00:32:02,091
even if you wake up one day

358
00:32:03,384 --> 00:32:05,345
and dislike me.

359
00:32:05,970 --> 00:32:09,766
A change of mind is not a valid reason
to get a refund. That's a given.

360
00:32:14,187 --> 00:32:15,688
Even if we get

361
00:32:16,856 --> 00:32:18,858
into huge fights

362
00:32:19,776 --> 00:32:20,985
and you're sick of me…

363
00:32:21,945 --> 00:32:25,907
Even if you claim that you don't remember
making this promise,

364
00:32:25,990 --> 00:32:27,241
there's no taking back.

365
00:32:28,159 --> 00:32:29,619
I'll still be by your side.

366
00:32:29,702 --> 00:32:31,579
All right. Fine. Do that.

367
00:32:33,998 --> 00:32:34,916
So stop talking.

368
00:32:45,468 --> 00:32:48,179
I love it the most

369
00:32:49,514 --> 00:32:52,433
when I can just focus on your heartbeat.

370
00:33:22,005 --> 00:33:24,007
I did some calculations.

371
00:33:24,090 --> 00:33:26,801
Five percent would be
forty-five billion won.

372
00:33:26,884 --> 00:33:28,511
But I'll just ask for 40 billion.

373
00:33:28,594 --> 00:33:31,389
I even have a car waiting outside
in case it's cash.

374
00:33:31,472 --> 00:33:33,016
-A big one.
-Are you a creditor?

375
00:33:34,142 --> 00:33:36,853
I may sound rude for saying this,

376
00:33:36,936 --> 00:33:41,065
but perhaps our history
made me into who I am today.

377
00:33:41,149 --> 00:33:44,736
I was betrayed several times
after doing all the work.

378
00:33:56,122 --> 00:33:57,123
Check.

379
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,253
KO JEONG-JA

380
00:34:04,714 --> 00:34:08,009
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten…

381
00:34:10,136 --> 00:34:11,971
I respect you, ma'am.

382
00:34:12,055 --> 00:34:15,058
A gorgeous face, a silver tongue,
and alluring charisma.

383
00:34:15,141 --> 00:34:17,560
It's rare for one to have all of them.

384
00:34:17,643 --> 00:34:21,022
I want to live wisely like you.

385
00:34:21,105 --> 00:34:23,191
-The payment is suspended.
-Sorry?

386
00:34:23,274 --> 00:34:25,860
You can only spend that money
when I let you.

387
00:34:25,943 --> 00:34:26,944
Ma'am.

388
00:34:27,737 --> 00:34:30,364
Our history made you
into who you are today?

389
00:34:30,448 --> 00:34:33,618
Likewise. I was betrayed several times.

390
00:34:33,701 --> 00:34:35,787
-Look.
-I'll lift the suspension

391
00:34:35,870 --> 00:34:39,457
once I'm content with your work.
Then you can take it.

392
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:40,541
Goodness.

393
00:34:41,334 --> 00:34:42,752
You sure are wise.

394
00:34:45,046 --> 00:34:46,089
Mom!

395
00:34:46,172 --> 00:34:49,092
What's all this?
It's not even kimchi-making season!

396
00:34:49,175 --> 00:34:51,594
Hae-in's family is leaving,
but I have nothing to give.

397
00:34:51,677 --> 00:34:53,429
I'll give them
some pear extract and kimchi.

398
00:34:53,513 --> 00:34:55,348
This isn't little at all.

399
00:34:55,431 --> 00:34:58,059
I thought I could share with our neighbors

400
00:34:58,142 --> 00:34:59,435
and the elderly.

401
00:34:59,519 --> 00:35:01,104
You can't do this alone.

402
00:35:01,187 --> 00:35:03,231
Then go get some gloves and help out.

403
00:35:03,314 --> 00:35:05,608
Well, I need these hands to make a living.

404
00:35:05,691 --> 00:35:07,902
Let me help.

405
00:35:07,985 --> 00:35:10,530
-Should I slice the radish?
-That'd be great.

406
00:35:14,033 --> 00:35:16,077
Jeez, she's so fast.

407
00:35:17,954 --> 00:35:19,705
She knows how to chop.

408
00:35:21,833 --> 00:35:25,461
Her chopping skills
were out of this world.

409
00:35:25,545 --> 00:35:26,712
-I see.
-I see.

410
00:35:26,796 --> 00:35:29,215
-And she has guts.
-Why?

411
00:35:38,266 --> 00:35:39,142
Hey.

412
00:35:39,225 --> 00:35:41,519
Do you think
I'll take you back if you do this?

413
00:35:42,061 --> 00:35:44,021
I don't expect you to.

414
00:35:44,105 --> 00:35:46,107
I'm going to leave once I'm done here.

415
00:35:46,816 --> 00:35:48,359
Don't worry, Mother.

416
00:35:49,068 --> 00:35:51,237
Yet you still call me that.

417
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:53,614
Are you teasing me? Don't call me that.

418
00:35:54,615 --> 00:35:55,491
But I'd like to.

419
00:35:57,660 --> 00:35:58,578
What?

420
00:35:59,495 --> 00:36:03,124
You're the first person
I ever called "Mother."

421
00:36:03,207 --> 00:36:04,584
So please let me do that.

422
00:36:10,506 --> 00:36:12,592
-Here you go.
-Hey.

423
00:36:12,675 --> 00:36:13,885
-Are you done?
-Anything else?

424
00:36:13,968 --> 00:36:15,303
That's enough.

425
00:36:16,179 --> 00:36:17,555
I'll chop the green onions.

426
00:36:21,934 --> 00:36:22,768
Unbelievable.

427
00:36:22,852 --> 00:36:25,605
-I kind of like her.
-Why?

428
00:36:25,688 --> 00:36:28,774
I like how she's not intimidated
and speaks her mind

429
00:36:28,858 --> 00:36:30,526
in front of her mother-in-law.

430
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,783
Hae-in.

431
00:36:37,867 --> 00:36:40,161
Come sit. They all heard

432
00:36:40,244 --> 00:36:42,788
about your surgery and were happy for you.

433
00:36:42,872 --> 00:36:43,831
I'm so happy for you.

434
00:36:43,915 --> 00:36:45,875
-I'm glad.
-It all worked out.

435
00:36:45,958 --> 00:36:46,876
Thank you.

436
00:36:47,627 --> 00:36:48,461
By the way,

437
00:36:50,087 --> 00:36:51,756
what were you doing?

438
00:36:51,839 --> 00:36:55,968
Right. Have you done this before?
Dyeing your nails with balsam?

439
00:36:56,928 --> 00:36:59,222
-No.
-Legend has it that if your nails

440
00:36:59,305 --> 00:37:02,308
are still colored by the first snow,
your first love will come true.

441
00:37:02,391 --> 00:37:06,020
That's why Bang-sil here always dyes hers
in the fall, not summer.

442
00:37:07,104 --> 00:37:07,980
How romantic.

443
00:37:08,064 --> 00:37:11,359
Actually, I'd say
she has an ulterior motive.

444
00:37:12,109 --> 00:37:14,362
I wouldn't say it's an ulterior motive.

445
00:37:14,445 --> 00:37:16,572
He happens to be divorced.

446
00:37:17,531 --> 00:37:19,825
-Hey.
-I didn't feel like this before,

447
00:37:19,909 --> 00:37:22,620
but we've been running
into each other often lately.

448
00:37:22,703 --> 00:37:23,579
So my feelings…

449
00:37:23,663 --> 00:37:25,164
Shut that mouth of yours.

450
00:37:25,248 --> 00:37:26,457
-That's enough.
-Stop.

451
00:37:26,540 --> 00:37:27,959
-Shut it.
-Sorry.

452
00:37:28,042 --> 00:37:31,963
I guess I was too blunt.
I hope you're not offended, Ms. Hong.

453
00:37:32,463 --> 00:37:34,215
-Why would I be?
-You see…

454
00:37:34,715 --> 00:37:37,051
Hyun-woo used to flirt a lot with me

455
00:37:37,134 --> 00:37:40,054
at church back when he was in high school.

456
00:37:40,137 --> 00:37:42,348
When did he ever do that?

457
00:37:42,431 --> 00:37:43,724
Didn't you know?

458
00:37:43,808 --> 00:37:46,352
They used to hand out snacks at church,

459
00:37:46,435 --> 00:37:51,232
and he'd always give me more than one

460
00:37:51,315 --> 00:37:52,358
in front of everyone.

461
00:37:52,441 --> 00:37:55,361
That's because
you always ate other kids' snacks.

462
00:37:55,987 --> 00:37:58,114
Hae-in, please don't misunderstand.

463
00:37:58,197 --> 00:38:00,866
Don't talk such nonsense, Bang-sil.

464
00:38:05,288 --> 00:38:07,123
Until the first snow, was it?

465
00:38:49,081 --> 00:38:50,750
-Check this out.
-Balsam?

466
00:38:51,584 --> 00:38:53,252
It's not that simple.

467
00:38:54,128 --> 00:38:56,422
-Then?
-It signifies my excitement, hope,

468
00:38:56,505 --> 00:38:59,884
and anticipation for the first snow
that I thought I'd never see.

469
00:39:00,801 --> 00:39:02,887
I didn't think I'd ever see winter again

470
00:39:02,970 --> 00:39:05,556
let alone the first snow.

471
00:39:05,639 --> 00:39:07,475
But it's possible now.

472
00:39:10,394 --> 00:39:11,395
Of course.

473
00:39:12,271 --> 00:39:16,025
And it'll come true
if the color still remains by then.

474
00:39:16,734 --> 00:39:18,486
-What will come true?
-My first love.

475
00:39:19,862 --> 00:39:22,448
By "first love,"

476
00:39:23,115 --> 00:39:26,452
do you mean that guy
on the bus or taxi from before?

477
00:39:26,535 --> 00:39:29,789
You're happy to watch them from afar.
You can't stop thinking about them.

478
00:39:29,872 --> 00:39:32,249
You take a detour
just to see them once more.

479
00:39:32,333 --> 00:39:34,085
You were happy to watch him from afar.

480
00:39:34,168 --> 00:39:35,961
You couldn't stop thinking about him.

481
00:39:36,045 --> 00:39:38,547
And you took a detour
just to see him once more.

482
00:39:38,631 --> 00:39:40,341
That bastard?

483
00:39:40,424 --> 00:39:42,218
Why are you cursing him?

484
00:39:44,220 --> 00:39:45,054
Fine.

485
00:39:45,596 --> 00:39:46,847
-That guy?
-Yes.

486
00:39:47,556 --> 00:39:50,601
I hope it'll snow sooner

487
00:39:50,684 --> 00:39:52,186
this year.

488
00:39:54,772 --> 00:39:57,608
Hae-in, you even took my ring back.

489
00:39:57,691 --> 00:39:59,735
Your first love shouldn't come true,

490
00:39:59,819 --> 00:40:01,695
or it'll really complicate things.

491
00:40:02,696 --> 00:40:03,572
Are you listening?

492
00:40:05,116 --> 00:40:06,117
Hae-in.

493
00:40:14,417 --> 00:40:18,421
-Michael met with Hong Beom-seok?
-Yes, as the CEO of Ever H.

494
00:40:18,504 --> 00:40:22,007
I guess the eldest son wants to return
now that his father is dead.

495
00:40:22,091 --> 00:40:23,134
Ever H recently appeared

496
00:40:23,217 --> 00:40:25,970
on the stockholder's list
as a non-institutional investor.

497
00:40:26,053 --> 00:40:28,806
He must've been gathering stocks
ever since they plummeted.

498
00:40:28,889 --> 00:40:30,975
He's been asking
the anchor LPs for my spot.

499
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:34,228
He can try, but you'll be safe
with what I've given you.

500
00:40:35,146 --> 00:40:36,272
As you said,

501
00:40:36,355 --> 00:40:38,941
we founded paper companies
in Hong Kong and Switzerland

502
00:40:39,024 --> 00:40:42,361
and opened up an IEBC business account.

503
00:40:42,445 --> 00:40:45,781
You're the only one who can manage it.

504
00:40:50,369 --> 00:40:54,081
-What will your first transaction be?
-Make it 2.1% in CD.

505
00:40:54,165 --> 00:40:55,624
CD(CAREFUL DISCRETION): BUYING SMALL
AMOUNTS OF STOCK AT REGULAR INTERVALS

506
00:40:55,708 --> 00:40:57,251
-Yes, sir.
-He took the bait.

507
00:40:57,334 --> 00:40:59,253
He's finally using the secret fund.

508
00:41:00,504 --> 00:41:03,757
He's probably worried
that my uncle might take his spot.

509
00:41:04,508 --> 00:41:06,427
Is Mr. Hong still in New York?

510
00:41:06,510 --> 00:41:08,387
Yes, he's still meeting with the LPs.

511
00:41:08,471 --> 00:41:11,140
Keep Eun-sung in the loop

512
00:41:11,223 --> 00:41:14,018
so that he'll feel anxious
and use the secret fund to buy stocks.

513
00:41:14,101 --> 00:41:15,853
-Yes, sir.
-Once we have concrete proof,

514
00:41:15,936 --> 00:41:18,981
we can charge him for embezzlement,
malpractice, and violating

515
00:41:19,064 --> 00:41:20,524
foreign exchange transaction laws.

516
00:41:21,275 --> 00:41:22,651
By the way,

517
00:41:22,735 --> 00:41:24,820
about that guy, Pyeon Seong-uk…

518
00:41:24,904 --> 00:41:27,573
Isn't he the land broker
who kidnapped you?

519
00:41:27,656 --> 00:41:29,700
Yes, he had agreed to hand over

520
00:41:29,783 --> 00:41:32,536
the double contract
and information on Director Jo.

521
00:41:32,620 --> 00:41:34,914
But he never showed up,
and I can't reach him.

522
00:41:34,997 --> 00:41:38,417
He hasn't been spending any money
or using his phone for over a week now.

523
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:40,794
Maybe he stowed away.

524
00:41:47,468 --> 00:41:48,344
Oh, God!

525
00:41:48,427 --> 00:41:51,096
A man, presumably in his 40s,
was found dead last night

526
00:41:51,180 --> 00:41:54,308
near the Sambang Reservoir
in Yeongjin-gun, Gyeonggi Province.

527
00:41:54,391 --> 00:41:55,976
He had been stabbed with a weapon,

528
00:41:56,060 --> 00:41:59,063
and his identity remains unknown
due to severe decomposition--

529
00:42:09,031 --> 00:42:11,325
How could this be mine,
but not mine at the same time?

530
00:42:20,584 --> 00:42:21,877
Ms. Kim!

531
00:42:21,961 --> 00:42:24,463
The amazing Grace is here!

532
00:42:24,547 --> 00:42:26,090
Jeez, why is she back?

533
00:42:26,715 --> 00:42:28,008
What are you doing?

534
00:42:28,092 --> 00:42:29,927
Can't you see?
I'm making dried persimmons.

535
00:42:30,010 --> 00:42:30,886
Goodness.

536
00:42:31,887 --> 00:42:34,056
Your hands have gotten rough.

537
00:42:34,765 --> 00:42:36,016
Look at those dark circles.

538
00:42:36,559 --> 00:42:39,144
All the freckles
I worked hard to erase are back.

539
00:42:42,898 --> 00:42:45,067
You'll be making a comeback soon.

540
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:46,819
It's a battlefield there.

541
00:42:46,902 --> 00:42:49,238
Everyone will take sides between Ms. Moh,

542
00:42:49,321 --> 00:42:50,948
that sly fox, and you.

543
00:42:51,031 --> 00:42:53,909
What's the best way
to intimidate your opponent?

544
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:57,538
With your face, of course.
Lie down right now.

545
00:42:57,621 --> 00:43:00,040
You need to look tight and radiant.

546
00:43:06,547 --> 00:43:10,426
I've never done this before.
It's ticklish.

547
00:43:10,509 --> 00:43:14,013
Don't smile, or you'll get wrinkles.
Keep these words in mind.

548
00:43:14,096 --> 00:43:17,057
Whitening, resilience,
recovery, and comeback.

549
00:43:17,141 --> 00:43:20,269
The best way to make a comeback
is through recovery and resilience.

550
00:43:20,352 --> 00:43:23,188
Don't worry.
Everything will go back to its place.

551
00:43:23,272 --> 00:43:25,274
We'll return to Queens,

552
00:43:25,357 --> 00:43:27,776
and Hae-in will get surgery
and become healthy again.

553
00:43:28,444 --> 00:43:30,237
Is she getting surgery?

554
00:43:30,321 --> 00:43:32,698
I thought surgery wasn't an option.

555
00:43:32,781 --> 00:43:34,950
We found a hospital that could do it.

556
00:43:35,034 --> 00:43:36,952
She'll be leaving for Germany soon.

557
00:43:37,036 --> 00:43:37,953
Is that so?

558
00:43:39,580 --> 00:43:40,998
I'm so glad.

559
00:43:41,081 --> 00:43:43,250
-Right?
-Right?

560
00:44:07,107 --> 00:44:09,068
Hello, I wanted to see you.

561
00:44:09,735 --> 00:44:10,944
-See me?
-Yes.

562
00:44:11,904 --> 00:44:13,697
-I have something for you.
-What is it?

563
00:44:13,781 --> 00:44:16,617
But I didn't think I'd run into you,
so it's at home.

564
00:44:16,700 --> 00:44:17,826
Shall we meet tonight?

565
00:44:18,744 --> 00:44:20,079
-At night?
-Yes.

566
00:44:21,789 --> 00:44:23,624
Sure then.

567
00:44:31,965 --> 00:44:34,009
Why does he want to meet at this hour?

568
00:44:37,012 --> 00:44:39,181
He's such a go-getter.

569
00:44:39,264 --> 00:44:40,307
He's dangerous.

570
00:44:46,563 --> 00:44:48,148
You were here already.

571
00:44:52,403 --> 00:44:53,237
Yes.

572
00:44:55,239 --> 00:44:57,408
-So I--
-Let me go first.

573
00:44:57,491 --> 00:44:58,534
Okay. I'm listening.

574
00:44:58,617 --> 00:44:59,535
I'll be leaving

575
00:45:00,703 --> 00:45:02,371
tomorrow.

576
00:45:02,454 --> 00:45:04,957
And I don't know when I'll ever revisit.

577
00:45:05,040 --> 00:45:07,209
I heard that you were leaving so--

578
00:45:07,292 --> 00:45:08,877
I know what you want to say.

579
00:45:08,961 --> 00:45:13,424
I caught onto it

580
00:45:13,507 --> 00:45:16,218
from the mulberry incident.

581
00:45:17,344 --> 00:45:18,679
-But no.
-Sorry?

582
00:45:19,346 --> 00:45:20,180
What do you--

583
00:45:20,264 --> 00:45:21,306
I have

584
00:45:21,932 --> 00:45:23,225
a lot on my plate.

585
00:45:23,308 --> 00:45:26,186
Not only do I have movable assets,
real estate, stocks, and bonds,

586
00:45:27,312 --> 00:45:28,772
but I also have three ex-husbands.

587
00:45:30,774 --> 00:45:32,025
I had no idea.

588
00:45:32,735 --> 00:45:34,027
Right?

589
00:45:34,111 --> 00:45:35,362
Anyway…

590
00:45:35,446 --> 00:45:36,447
I'm complicated

591
00:45:37,740 --> 00:45:39,616
and carry many burdens.

592
00:45:40,617 --> 00:45:41,702
So I can't

593
00:45:42,578 --> 00:45:43,579
accept it.

594
00:45:45,539 --> 00:45:47,374
I hope you still will.

595
00:45:49,042 --> 00:45:49,960
What is this?

596
00:45:51,754 --> 00:45:53,088
Did you write a letter?

597
00:45:55,632 --> 00:45:58,177
You really shouldn't…

598
00:45:58,260 --> 00:45:59,261
CONDOLENCES
KIM YEONG-SONG

599
00:45:59,344 --> 00:46:00,763
It's condolence money.

600
00:46:00,846 --> 00:46:02,514
I heard about your father.

601
00:46:07,770 --> 00:46:09,897
I don't need this.

602
00:46:09,980 --> 00:46:11,148
-I should go.
-No, wait.

603
00:46:11,231 --> 00:46:13,233
Come on. This isn't right.

604
00:46:13,317 --> 00:46:15,194
This isn't for you.

605
00:46:15,277 --> 00:46:17,613
It's for your father.

606
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:22,534
Even the wealthiest
start off with no money in the afterlife.

607
00:46:26,205 --> 00:46:28,665
It's not much, but I'm sure

608
00:46:29,333 --> 00:46:32,169
he'll be able to enjoy
some rice soup and drinks tonight

609
00:46:32,252 --> 00:46:33,754
with his friends.

610
00:46:38,425 --> 00:46:40,844
He'll be enjoying good food

611
00:46:40,928 --> 00:46:44,139
and having a great time with his friends.

612
00:46:44,223 --> 00:46:45,974
So don't be too sad.

613
00:46:49,853 --> 00:46:50,979
Thank you.

614
00:46:53,065 --> 00:46:54,566
Goodbye.

615
00:47:06,787 --> 00:47:07,913
Goodbye.

616
00:47:27,015 --> 00:47:28,141
What do you mean?

617
00:47:28,225 --> 00:47:30,018
You want to stay here?

618
00:47:31,395 --> 00:47:32,354
I'm dumbfounded.

619
00:47:32,437 --> 00:47:34,940
It's temporary.
Just until we find a place in Seoul.

620
00:47:35,023 --> 00:47:37,651
Your mother doesn't understand
why you need to find a place.

621
00:47:37,734 --> 00:47:41,864
I've had two training wheels
throughout my whole life.

622
00:47:41,947 --> 00:47:42,781
One was you.

623
00:47:44,032 --> 00:47:45,742
And the other one was you.

624
00:47:45,826 --> 00:47:47,160
What are you saying?

625
00:47:47,953 --> 00:47:49,037
But now,

626
00:47:49,913 --> 00:47:52,791
I want to remove them
and stand on my own two feet.

627
00:47:52,875 --> 00:47:55,168
Don't be ridiculous.

628
00:47:55,752 --> 00:47:57,254
Hey, did you persuade him?

629
00:47:57,337 --> 00:47:59,631
-Did you urge him again?
-Honey, be quiet.

630
00:47:59,715 --> 00:48:01,008
Don't say a thing.

631
00:48:01,091 --> 00:48:02,301
Plead the Fifth.

632
00:48:03,051 --> 00:48:05,512
You're forbidden
from speaking to her directly.

633
00:48:05,596 --> 00:48:07,347
-If you want, speak to our attorney.
-What?

634
00:48:07,431 --> 00:48:10,017
-Please do that, Hyun-woo.
-Sorry, but I refuse.

635
00:48:10,934 --> 00:48:13,103
Hey, you can take care
of your own family issues.

636
00:48:13,186 --> 00:48:15,397
Since we're on this topic,
let me say something too.

637
00:48:16,565 --> 00:48:17,774
I'm not going home either.

638
00:48:18,483 --> 00:48:19,318
You too?

639
00:48:19,401 --> 00:48:21,987
We're moving
into his studio apartment in Seoul.

640
00:48:22,654 --> 00:48:25,407
We'll be leaving for Germany soon,
and it's closer to the airport.

641
00:48:25,490 --> 00:48:27,200
No, it's actually farther from there.

642
00:48:27,284 --> 00:48:29,328
Best of all, it's newly built
and fully furnished.

643
00:48:29,411 --> 00:48:31,455
It has everything we need
in that small area.

644
00:48:31,538 --> 00:48:32,915
But back home,

645
00:48:32,998 --> 00:48:35,042
we need to take the elevator
to reach the kitchen.

646
00:48:35,125 --> 00:48:37,669
It just takes way too long.

647
00:48:37,753 --> 00:48:39,713
Hey, your excuses are lengthier.

648
00:48:39,796 --> 00:48:42,049
You just want some alone time.

649
00:48:42,132 --> 00:48:43,175
Yes, ma'am.

650
00:48:43,717 --> 00:48:45,844
I'd like to spend
some time with her alone.

651
00:48:49,723 --> 00:48:50,807
Please let us do that.

652
00:48:50,891 --> 00:48:53,769
Sure, if that's more comfortable for you.

653
00:48:53,852 --> 00:48:55,312
Sure, you can do that.

654
00:48:55,395 --> 00:48:57,814
Let me know if you need anything.

655
00:48:58,982 --> 00:48:59,816
Gosh.

656
00:48:59,900 --> 00:49:02,069
Is this what discrimination feels like?

657
00:49:02,152 --> 00:49:04,488
This is my first time experiencing it.

658
00:49:04,571 --> 00:49:05,948
It's something new, though.

659
00:49:06,448 --> 00:49:08,492
They're packing up and returning tomorrow.

660
00:49:08,575 --> 00:49:10,202
You should be ready for them.

661
00:49:11,411 --> 00:49:13,538
I also met with Da-hye.

662
00:49:16,083 --> 00:49:17,084
What is this?

663
00:49:17,167 --> 00:49:18,335
Why did you come back?

664
00:49:18,418 --> 00:49:20,212
Don't let Ms. Moh know.

665
00:49:20,295 --> 00:49:21,421
You idiot.

666
00:49:21,505 --> 00:49:24,299
She was the one who told me you were here.

667
00:49:24,383 --> 00:49:25,258
Seriously?

668
00:49:25,342 --> 00:49:27,344
She knows how you came here

669
00:49:27,427 --> 00:49:30,430
in a taxi with the golden Buddha
in the middle of the night.

670
00:49:30,514 --> 00:49:32,307
Her men are watching you.

671
00:49:32,391 --> 00:49:34,267
So tell me. Why are you here?

672
00:49:34,351 --> 00:49:35,894
Is it guilt or a grudge?

673
00:49:37,062 --> 00:49:38,647
What grudge could I have?

674
00:49:38,730 --> 00:49:39,856
It's my conscience.

675
00:49:39,940 --> 00:49:41,233
I didn't know you had one.

676
00:49:42,150 --> 00:49:43,443
Me neither.

677
00:49:43,527 --> 00:49:47,322
He was the first person
to love me for who I was, and I felt bad.

678
00:49:47,406 --> 00:49:48,615
Goodness.

679
00:49:48,699 --> 00:49:49,741
Unbelievable.

680
00:49:49,825 --> 00:49:51,201
He grew on her.

681
00:49:51,284 --> 00:49:55,247
I'm sure you know
that those feelings can't be stopped.

682
00:49:55,330 --> 00:49:58,041
How dare she betray me
after all I've done for her?

683
00:49:58,125 --> 00:50:00,794
This is exactly why
you shouldn't trust people.

684
00:50:01,461 --> 00:50:03,588
And about Hae-in…

685
00:50:03,672 --> 00:50:06,049
She might be able to save herself.

686
00:50:06,133 --> 00:50:07,718
She's getting surgery.

687
00:50:07,801 --> 00:50:09,302
Hyun-woo looked everywhere for help,

688
00:50:09,386 --> 00:50:11,471
and they finally found
a hospital that can help.

689
00:50:11,555 --> 00:50:13,682
They're leaving for Germany next week.

690
00:50:19,813 --> 00:50:21,314
You startled me.

691
00:50:23,108 --> 00:50:26,194
Find out which hospital
and what kind of surgery she's receiving.

692
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:32,659
What are you doing?

693
00:50:32,743 --> 00:50:33,577
Nothing much.

694
00:50:34,411 --> 00:50:35,704
I can see many stars.

695
00:50:44,463 --> 00:50:46,798
I even saw a shooting star recently.

696
00:50:48,383 --> 00:50:49,217
Really?

697
00:50:50,635 --> 00:50:53,513
I dreamed of one
when I was pregnant with you.

698
00:50:54,347 --> 00:50:56,850
I always wanted a pretty daughter.

699
00:50:57,517 --> 00:50:58,810
I was ecstatic…

700
00:51:01,146 --> 00:51:02,564
after having that dream.

701
00:51:13,116 --> 00:51:16,078
I don't know which attitude to take.

702
00:51:17,245 --> 00:51:20,874
We were like cats and dogs
for over 20 years,

703
00:51:20,957 --> 00:51:24,377
so I feel awkward to suddenly act
so affectionate toward you.

704
00:51:25,712 --> 00:51:26,713
But deep down,

705
00:51:28,965 --> 00:51:30,258
I feel so guilty

706
00:51:31,259 --> 00:51:32,719
and regretful.

707
00:51:32,803 --> 00:51:33,929
I want to treat you well.

708
00:51:35,972 --> 00:51:37,015
This is good enough.

709
00:51:41,394 --> 00:51:42,229
Is it?

710
00:51:42,312 --> 00:51:45,148
I'd feel awkward, too,
if you suddenly changed your ways.

711
00:51:45,232 --> 00:51:47,776
We'll have a lot of time,

712
00:51:47,859 --> 00:51:49,236
so let's take it slowly.

713
00:51:51,947 --> 00:51:54,116
This will do for now.

714
00:51:54,866 --> 00:51:55,867
All right.

715
00:51:56,993 --> 00:52:02,165
Once you return from Germany,
we can gradually warm up to each other.

716
00:52:14,553 --> 00:52:16,555
I didn't know it was this suffocating

717
00:52:16,638 --> 00:52:18,181
to act as a mediator.

718
00:52:18,807 --> 00:52:21,935
Right. They say it's just as stressful
as joining the military.

719
00:52:22,018 --> 00:52:25,021
We need to move out of the house
if I want to protect Da-hye

720
00:52:25,105 --> 00:52:26,731
from my mom.

721
00:52:28,441 --> 00:52:30,694
Gosh. What's taking them so long?

722
00:52:31,486 --> 00:52:32,487
Mom, Dad.

723
00:52:33,155 --> 00:52:34,197
I packed your stuff.

724
00:52:34,281 --> 00:52:35,740
Really? Okay.

725
00:52:37,325 --> 00:52:40,495
You'll run into traffic soon,
so you should go now. Hurry.

726
00:52:45,083 --> 00:52:46,960
I'm sorry for all the inconvenience,

727
00:52:47,043 --> 00:52:50,046
but I feel the most guilty
about leaving him behind.

728
00:52:50,130 --> 00:52:52,382
It feels like leaving

729
00:52:52,465 --> 00:52:54,843
a bag of trash behind after a trip.

730
00:52:54,926 --> 00:52:56,761
-Father--
-Gosh, don't worry.

731
00:52:57,470 --> 00:52:59,764
And why are you in a hurry?

732
00:52:59,848 --> 00:53:01,766
Have lunch with us.

733
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:02,767
Should we?

734
00:53:02,851 --> 00:53:05,520
No! Our house has been empty
for over a month now.

735
00:53:05,604 --> 00:53:06,938
There's a lot to take care of.

736
00:53:07,022 --> 00:53:09,649
-I was going to make kimchi pancakes.
-It's okay.

737
00:53:09,733 --> 00:53:10,650
Kimchi pancakes?

738
00:53:10,734 --> 00:53:14,404
How about some crispy kimchi pancakes
and delicious makgeolli?

739
00:53:14,487 --> 00:53:16,698
That's ridiculous. He needs to drive.

740
00:53:16,781 --> 00:53:18,366
I can drive instead.

741
00:53:19,367 --> 00:53:22,621
Or better yet, you can leave tomorrow.

742
00:53:22,704 --> 00:53:24,623
-You should.
-We could.

743
00:53:24,706 --> 00:53:28,376
Do you know how beautiful it is

744
00:53:28,460 --> 00:53:30,337
to know when to leave?

745
00:53:30,420 --> 00:53:31,755
Must I know that?

746
00:53:32,422 --> 00:53:33,590
We'll get going first.

747
00:53:34,591 --> 00:53:36,051
We don't want to run into traffic.

748
00:53:36,134 --> 00:53:38,511
Okay, you should go before then.

749
00:53:39,137 --> 00:53:42,015
Thank you for everything. Goodbye.

750
00:53:43,767 --> 00:53:46,311
Good luck with the surgery.

751
00:53:47,270 --> 00:53:48,230
Hae-in.

752
00:53:48,897 --> 00:53:49,898
Let's meet again.

753
00:54:02,369 --> 00:54:03,203
Hyun-woo.

754
00:54:03,995 --> 00:54:04,955
I trust you.

755
00:54:06,373 --> 00:54:07,207
Don't worry.

756
00:54:07,916 --> 00:54:08,750
Here.

757
00:54:09,793 --> 00:54:12,879
Your mom made
some kimchi and pear extract.

758
00:54:12,963 --> 00:54:13,964
Carry it for him.

759
00:54:14,047 --> 00:54:15,632
Should I? Give it to me.

760
00:54:15,715 --> 00:54:16,841
Goodbye.

761
00:54:26,643 --> 00:54:27,644
Mom, your handbag…

762
00:54:41,908 --> 00:54:43,743
You're the bachelor on the 11th floor.

763
00:54:43,827 --> 00:54:44,828
-Hello.
-Hi.

764
00:54:49,124 --> 00:54:50,500
He's not a bachelor.

765
00:54:52,877 --> 00:54:53,920
I'm his wife.

766
00:54:55,505 --> 00:54:57,465
Didn't you say

767
00:54:57,549 --> 00:54:59,467
you were living here by yourself?

768
00:54:59,551 --> 00:55:01,928
Did you get married recently?

769
00:55:03,722 --> 00:55:05,432
-Yes.
-Goodness!

770
00:55:05,515 --> 00:55:08,351
You're newlyweds!

771
00:55:08,935 --> 00:55:11,688
You must be so happy.

772
00:55:11,771 --> 00:55:13,565
Yes, we are.

773
00:55:33,418 --> 00:55:36,671
It's official that we're newlyweds now.

774
00:55:37,714 --> 00:55:39,674
Why is it official?

775
00:55:39,758 --> 00:55:41,426
Because of that lady.

776
00:55:41,509 --> 00:55:45,889
A woman like her will tell everyone
in this building about us by tomorrow.

777
00:55:46,848 --> 00:55:51,978
"The bachelor on the 11th floor
married a gorgeous woman."

778
00:55:54,981 --> 00:55:56,858
Okay. So?

779
00:55:58,109 --> 00:56:03,031
We should act like newlyweds then.

780
00:56:08,244 --> 00:56:09,245
How?

781
00:56:32,102 --> 00:56:34,437
Normally, newlyweds in love

782
00:56:34,521 --> 00:56:36,856
are always touching each other somehow.

783
00:56:50,829 --> 00:56:53,248
It could be their hands, feet,

784
00:57:02,757 --> 00:57:03,591
or shoulders.

785
00:57:06,886 --> 00:57:07,887
Anything.

786
00:57:10,598 --> 00:57:12,642
They stick by each other

787
00:57:13,226 --> 00:57:15,770
and spend their everyday lives together.

788
00:57:16,688 --> 00:57:18,773
We're bound to run
into hardships again one day.

789
00:57:18,857 --> 00:57:20,442
I'm nervous. Did you smile?

790
00:57:20,525 --> 00:57:22,235
Then we can pull out these happy memories

791
00:57:22,318 --> 00:57:26,114
as if they're candies in a candy jar

792
00:57:26,823 --> 00:57:29,117
and endure those moments.

793
00:57:29,993 --> 00:57:31,953
That's why we need to gather

794
00:57:32,036 --> 00:57:34,247
as many good memories
as possible right now.

795
00:57:44,716 --> 00:57:45,550
That looks tasty.

796
00:58:06,779 --> 00:58:10,033
I'm going to focus more
on collecting happy memories

797
00:58:10,116 --> 00:58:12,911
than stocks or money from now on.

798
00:58:12,994 --> 00:58:15,038
The most important thing for me now

799
00:58:15,997 --> 00:58:17,415
is filling up my candy jar.

800
00:58:23,713 --> 00:58:25,632
Why did you come here so often?

801
00:58:25,715 --> 00:58:27,258
Is baseball that fun?

802
00:58:29,177 --> 00:58:30,512
That's not why.

803
00:58:31,137 --> 00:58:34,807
All I need to focus on
is hitting the ball.

804
00:58:34,891 --> 00:58:36,351
That's what I liked.

805
00:58:38,853 --> 00:58:39,896
Does that

806
00:58:41,272 --> 00:58:42,440
make you feel better?

807
00:58:42,524 --> 00:58:48,655
Well… It was nice to focus on one thing
when things were complicated.

808
00:58:49,864 --> 00:58:52,742
I just need to concentrate

809
00:58:53,952 --> 00:58:55,411
on what's the most important.

810
00:58:55,495 --> 00:58:57,080
And what is that

811
00:58:57,830 --> 00:58:59,374
right now?

812
00:59:03,962 --> 00:59:05,588
Saving you, of course.

813
00:59:09,467 --> 00:59:10,843
That's all that matters.

814
00:59:12,845 --> 00:59:14,430
I'll only focus on that.

815
00:59:33,491 --> 00:59:36,119
Soo-cheol is staying
in Yongdu-ri for some time.

816
00:59:36,202 --> 00:59:39,205
Hae-in decided to stay with Hyun-woo too.

817
00:59:39,289 --> 00:59:42,375
Only the vice-chairman
and his wife are returning.

818
00:59:42,959 --> 00:59:44,002
The vice-chairman?

819
00:59:44,877 --> 00:59:46,212
I'm sorry.

820
00:59:46,296 --> 00:59:49,215
But now that they have their shares,

821
00:59:49,299 --> 00:59:52,385
wouldn't he want
to take back his position?

822
00:59:54,512 --> 00:59:55,388
Says who?

823
00:59:56,556 --> 00:59:59,434
They'll regret coming back here.

824
01:00:11,404 --> 01:00:12,864
I was meaning to see you.

825
01:00:13,364 --> 01:00:15,033
Can we talk?

826
01:00:16,534 --> 01:00:18,494
I heard Hae-in
is getting surgery in Germany.

827
01:00:19,871 --> 01:00:21,205
Don't be so alarmed.

828
01:00:21,289 --> 01:00:22,665
I'm just happy for her.

829
01:00:23,249 --> 01:00:25,918
Is that so?

830
01:00:26,002 --> 01:00:26,836
Of course.

831
01:00:27,545 --> 01:00:31,090
I have feelings for her,
so it's natural for me to be happy

832
01:00:31,174 --> 01:00:32,091
that she can live.

833
01:00:33,134 --> 01:00:35,970
I heard you're going with her.
Please take care of her.

834
01:00:37,764 --> 01:00:38,765
Okay.

835
01:00:40,642 --> 01:00:41,851
Can I leave now?

836
01:00:43,519 --> 01:00:44,687
I found out

837
01:00:45,229 --> 01:00:47,982
that the surgery has a side effect.

838
01:00:54,030 --> 01:00:54,947
Does she know?

839
01:01:00,036 --> 01:01:01,079
Of course not.

840
01:01:01,162 --> 01:01:04,499
Given her personality, she'd refuse
to get the surgery if she knew.

841
01:01:06,501 --> 01:01:07,919
So she probably doesn't know.

842
01:01:08,002 --> 01:01:09,962
What are you getting at?

843
01:01:10,463 --> 01:01:12,882
Make sure you keep that secret

844
01:01:15,259 --> 01:01:16,678
so she gets the surgery.

845
01:01:17,970 --> 01:01:19,263
I told you.

846
01:01:20,056 --> 01:01:21,557
I want her to live.

847
01:01:31,859 --> 01:01:33,444
Remove all of their belongings.

848
01:01:33,528 --> 01:01:35,238
And give Mr. Baek back what's his.

849
01:01:59,971 --> 01:02:03,182
You wanted to come here
as a customer instead of the CEO,

850
01:02:03,266 --> 01:02:04,726
so I even took a leave.

851
01:02:04,809 --> 01:02:06,310
Yes, I'm here as a customer.

852
01:02:06,936 --> 01:02:08,813
-What'll you buy?
-I'm just looking.

853
01:02:08,896 --> 01:02:11,649
Didn't you hate those
who didn't buy anything?

854
01:02:13,901 --> 01:02:15,194
Is this a sauna?

855
01:02:15,278 --> 01:02:18,573
Why are they chatting
and not spending any money here?

856
01:02:18,656 --> 01:02:19,866
-Get rid of the chairs.
-Mom!

857
01:02:19,949 --> 01:02:22,160
-Mom!
-Mom!

858
01:02:23,244 --> 01:02:25,204
Why are they running around?

859
01:02:25,288 --> 01:02:27,999
They should do that at an amusement park.

860
01:02:28,082 --> 01:02:30,334
That's why
we got rid of all the rest zones.

861
01:02:30,418 --> 01:02:31,252
Fine.

862
01:02:31,836 --> 01:02:33,588
I'll spend some money then.

863
01:02:35,965 --> 01:02:37,049
Do you want anything?

864
01:02:37,675 --> 01:02:39,260
-What do you need?
-Lip balm.

865
01:02:40,178 --> 01:02:41,596
My lips are dry.

866
01:02:48,853 --> 01:02:50,605
Why am I so tired after shopping?

867
01:02:51,522 --> 01:02:52,523
Are you tired?

868
01:02:53,065 --> 01:02:54,150
That's not good.

869
01:02:54,233 --> 01:02:55,818
Let's go rest somewhere.

870
01:02:55,902 --> 01:02:56,944
No.

871
01:02:58,696 --> 01:02:59,697
This is good.

872
01:02:59,781 --> 01:03:02,742
The layout is incredible.
There's no time to rest.

873
01:03:02,825 --> 01:03:04,827
We shopped for lip balm
and bought cream too.

874
01:03:04,911 --> 01:03:07,079
We shopped for some knitwear
and bought a coat too.

875
01:03:07,163 --> 01:03:10,833
We didn't even plan on buying a muffler
or gloves, but we got them too.

876
01:03:10,917 --> 01:03:13,669
And now, the smell
of perfumes is alluring us.

877
01:03:13,753 --> 01:03:15,379
That was your strategy.

878
01:03:15,463 --> 01:03:18,007
You wanted to keep the customers busy.

879
01:03:18,090 --> 01:03:20,468
That's why you set up
so many pop-up stores.

880
01:03:21,427 --> 01:03:24,222
When I get reinstated,
I'm going to get rid of them.

881
01:03:24,305 --> 01:03:25,431
-Why?
-It's tiring.

882
01:03:26,390 --> 01:03:28,351
I feel stupid for spending money.

883
01:03:28,434 --> 01:03:29,268
I feel duped.

884
01:03:29,352 --> 01:03:31,020
Would you want to come back here?

885
01:03:31,103 --> 01:03:35,358
I'll get rid of them
and set up chairs once again.

886
01:03:35,441 --> 01:03:36,859
Expensive and comfortable ones.

887
01:03:37,652 --> 01:03:41,322
I'll renovate the square
on the first floor and hold concerts.

888
01:03:41,405 --> 01:03:44,200
There will be an area
where kids can run around.

889
01:03:44,283 --> 01:03:45,117
What?

890
01:03:45,618 --> 01:03:47,161
And a place for couples.

891
01:03:47,245 --> 01:03:48,663
The parents can bring

892
01:03:49,205 --> 01:03:51,541
their kids here
when it's cold or hot outside.

893
01:03:52,208 --> 01:03:53,501
It'd be nice.

894
01:03:54,001 --> 01:03:55,628
I will give them happiness.

895
01:03:55,711 --> 01:03:57,046
Seriously?

896
01:03:58,005 --> 01:03:58,881
Seriously.

897
01:03:58,965 --> 01:04:00,883
You better not take that back
after the surgery.

898
01:04:00,967 --> 01:04:01,801
Why would I?

899
01:04:01,884 --> 01:04:03,427
I saw it in the movies.

900
01:04:03,511 --> 01:04:06,389
Your personality can change
or you can lose your memory

901
01:04:06,472 --> 01:04:07,807
after a brain surgery.

902
01:04:07,890 --> 01:04:11,853
You're wrong. I just simply want
to become a slightly better person

903
01:04:12,436 --> 01:04:13,437
to reciprocate

904
01:04:14,188 --> 01:04:16,524
for being able to live longer.

905
01:04:20,027 --> 01:04:21,821
Mother.

906
01:04:28,160 --> 01:04:29,871
Isn't that your wife?

907
01:04:37,920 --> 01:04:38,838
Hello, Mother.

908
01:04:38,921 --> 01:04:42,508
Sweetie, what is that modest look
in your eyes?

909
01:04:42,592 --> 01:04:43,885
You're making me anxious.

910
01:04:45,386 --> 01:04:46,929
-Mother--
-I can't fix him.

911
01:04:47,013 --> 01:04:48,472
You can't return him!

912
01:04:48,556 --> 01:04:49,724
I'm sorry.

913
01:04:49,807 --> 01:04:51,726
I tried to keep our promise,

914
01:04:51,809 --> 01:04:53,978
but I'm afraid it's time.

915
01:04:58,274 --> 01:04:59,108
Fine.

916
01:04:59,775 --> 01:05:01,277
Let me hear your reason.

917
01:05:01,360 --> 01:05:02,653
-Tell her.
-Me?

918
01:05:06,198 --> 01:05:07,033
Right.

919
01:05:07,116 --> 01:05:10,745
I lied to you about attending a funeral
and spent the night gaming with friends.

920
01:05:14,040 --> 01:05:15,583
No? It's not that, Mom.

921
01:05:18,628 --> 01:05:19,462
Right.

922
01:05:19,545 --> 01:05:22,006
Did you find my game console?
It's secondhand. It's cheap.

923
01:05:22,089 --> 01:05:23,633
You even bought a game console?

924
01:05:27,803 --> 01:05:29,597
Can't you just tell me what it is?

925
01:05:30,598 --> 01:05:33,893
Mother, Hyeon-tae spent
our savings on buying stocks.

926
01:05:36,854 --> 01:05:37,855
He lost half of it.

927
01:05:38,522 --> 01:05:39,440
Hey!

928
01:05:40,858 --> 01:05:42,443
He even invested in cryptocurrency.

929
01:05:42,526 --> 01:05:44,654
It's minus 90% now.

930
01:05:44,737 --> 01:05:45,905
You lunatic.

931
01:05:47,657 --> 01:05:49,325
I'm sorry.

932
01:05:52,244 --> 01:05:53,079
Hyeon-suk.

933
01:05:53,621 --> 01:05:54,705
I don't know what to say.

934
01:05:55,414 --> 01:05:58,834
Return him to me, and I'll get rid of him.

935
01:05:58,918 --> 01:06:00,294
You should go on your way

936
01:06:00,378 --> 01:06:02,213
-while you still have time.
-Mom…

937
01:06:02,296 --> 01:06:03,297
Still,

938
01:06:04,215 --> 01:06:06,217
I'll text you when I make kimchi.

939
01:06:06,300 --> 01:06:07,551
So make sure you come.

940
01:06:07,635 --> 01:06:11,389
Even I think someone as wise
and pretty as you is out of his league.

941
01:06:12,264 --> 01:06:14,016
I'm truly sorry, Hyeon-suk.

942
01:06:15,434 --> 01:06:16,727
Mother…

943
01:06:21,816 --> 01:06:24,151
You need to come to your senses!

944
01:06:31,117 --> 01:06:31,951
Honey, I--

945
01:06:32,034 --> 01:06:33,035
Let me go!

946
01:06:39,625 --> 01:06:43,379
Honey, I think I'll be getting some money!

947
01:06:44,130 --> 01:06:47,633
Hae-in had bought a building,
but didn't have time to look at it.

948
01:06:48,467 --> 01:06:49,802
This must be it.

949
01:06:49,885 --> 01:06:52,847
Yes. I cleaned and swept
the building twice a day,

950
01:06:52,930 --> 01:06:55,474
waxed and washed all the signs,

951
01:06:55,558 --> 01:06:57,143
and disinfected the septic tanks.

952
01:06:57,226 --> 01:06:59,520
I'm also going to paint the building soon.

953
01:06:59,603 --> 01:07:00,438
I see.

954
01:07:00,521 --> 01:07:05,026
There's a good floating population
and visibility due to the two-lane road.

955
01:07:05,109 --> 01:07:06,694
It'd be easy to get rents.

956
01:07:06,777 --> 01:07:07,695
Yes, you're right.

957
01:07:07,778 --> 01:07:09,155
It's not bad at all.

958
01:07:09,238 --> 01:07:10,239
But why do you ask?

959
01:07:10,322 --> 01:07:12,033
Do you plan on selling it?

960
01:07:13,576 --> 01:07:15,494
I spoke with Hae-in.

961
01:07:16,412 --> 01:07:19,498
We'd like to gift the building to you.

962
01:07:24,211 --> 01:07:25,212
What did you say?

963
01:07:26,338 --> 01:07:29,383
Our tax accountant
will contact you once we go to Seoul

964
01:07:29,467 --> 01:07:31,677
and tell you what documents to prepare.

965
01:07:31,761 --> 01:07:33,012
But still,

966
01:07:33,554 --> 01:07:34,930
it's an entire building.

967
01:07:35,014 --> 01:07:36,348
It's a thank-you gift.

968
01:07:38,309 --> 01:07:41,729
Gosh, it's a huge gift.

969
01:07:43,189 --> 01:07:44,857
My parents will become building owners!

970
01:07:44,940 --> 01:07:46,525
Will you still return me?

971
01:07:50,279 --> 01:07:51,280
Honey.

972
01:07:51,363 --> 01:07:53,240
-You shouldn't be here.
-What?

973
01:07:55,826 --> 01:07:57,495
Go to the building owners.

974
01:08:02,583 --> 01:08:03,417
Hurry.

975
01:08:04,710 --> 01:08:07,088
I'm thinking
about renovating the first floor

976
01:08:07,171 --> 01:08:09,507
and setting up a fitness center.

977
01:08:09,590 --> 01:08:12,218
Hey, just focus on your current gym.

978
01:08:13,260 --> 01:08:16,680
Mom, I've been wanting
to relocate my hair salon.

979
01:08:16,764 --> 01:08:18,390
The first floor would be perfect.

980
01:08:18,474 --> 01:08:23,270
Don't butt in.
I was the one who cleaned and swept--

981
01:08:23,354 --> 01:08:26,440
I removed all the stickers on the stairs.
And you have the third floor.

982
01:08:26,524 --> 01:08:28,109
-Hyeon-tae.
-Yes, Mom?

983
01:08:28,192 --> 01:08:30,069
Get rid of the gym as soon as you can.

984
01:08:30,152 --> 01:08:33,030
Mom, that's a harsh joke.

985
01:08:33,114 --> 01:08:35,866
It's not a joke.
You haven't been paying rent.

986
01:08:35,950 --> 01:08:37,076
Come on, Mom.

987
01:08:37,660 --> 01:08:38,869
-Dad.
-Son.

988
01:08:39,453 --> 01:08:40,454
Yes?

989
01:08:45,376 --> 01:08:48,587
This is when a contract becomes useful.

990
01:08:49,505 --> 01:08:53,759
"If a tenant fails to pay rent
two times or more,

991
01:08:53,843 --> 01:08:55,427
the contract can be terminated."

992
01:08:55,511 --> 01:08:57,388
-Do you want to see?
-So what?

993
01:08:57,471 --> 01:08:59,515
-Are you kicking me out?
-No.

994
01:09:00,141 --> 01:09:02,226
I'm telling you to pay up.

995
01:09:02,309 --> 01:09:04,145
Pay on the tenth of every month.

996
01:09:04,228 --> 01:09:06,063
Dad.

997
01:09:06,147 --> 01:09:07,356
What about me?

998
01:09:07,439 --> 01:09:09,483
What about me?

999
01:09:09,567 --> 01:09:13,279
The first floor costs a million.
Move in if you can manage it.

1000
01:09:13,362 --> 01:09:15,990
That's more expensive
than my current rent.

1001
01:09:16,073 --> 01:09:17,533
Our building has a better location.

1002
01:09:17,616 --> 01:09:20,077
Anyway, we look forward

1003
01:09:20,161 --> 01:09:22,121
to this new tension between us,

1004
01:09:22,204 --> 01:09:24,165
thanks to this building.

1005
01:09:24,248 --> 01:09:25,166
We're very excited.

1006
01:09:25,249 --> 01:09:26,333
Come on, Dad.

1007
01:09:26,417 --> 01:09:28,878
We don't need tension in this family.

1008
01:09:28,961 --> 01:09:30,129
I do!

1009
01:09:30,212 --> 01:09:33,924
There were times
when I felt like you were impudent.

1010
01:09:34,008 --> 01:09:37,553
This building will prove

1011
01:09:37,636 --> 01:09:39,763
your loyalty to us.

1012
01:09:41,765 --> 01:09:43,392
-You're wrong.
-What?

1013
01:09:43,475 --> 01:09:46,187
I just want to receive rent.

1014
01:09:46,270 --> 01:09:47,688
Did you now?

1015
01:09:48,189 --> 01:09:49,773
You should've told me so.

1016
01:09:50,441 --> 01:09:51,567
Anyway…

1017
01:09:51,650 --> 01:09:52,818
-Our Dubong Building--
-What?

1018
01:09:52,902 --> 01:09:55,196
-What is that?
-Du-gwan and Bong-ae's building.

1019
01:09:55,988 --> 01:09:58,157
-Oh, my God.
-How tacky.

1020
01:09:58,240 --> 01:10:01,410
We expect you to pay rent religiously

1021
01:10:01,493 --> 01:10:04,663
despite being our children.

1022
01:10:05,623 --> 01:10:06,957
Keep that in mind.

1023
01:10:08,125 --> 01:10:11,170
It's only October,
but they're preparing for Christmas.

1024
01:10:11,253 --> 01:10:13,088
It was your order.

1025
01:10:14,506 --> 01:10:15,591
Mine?

1026
01:10:16,133 --> 01:10:18,385
Are you going to relax
because Chuseok is over?

1027
01:10:18,469 --> 01:10:20,387
Christmas is upcoming. Winter is coming.

1028
01:10:20,471 --> 01:10:22,681
We should liven up the mood

1029
01:10:22,765 --> 01:10:24,642
so they'll want to buy winter jackets.

1030
01:10:24,725 --> 01:10:26,936
We shouldn't wait
until the other stores begin.

1031
01:10:27,019 --> 01:10:30,147
We need to prepare in advance
and start the Christmas sale

1032
01:10:30,231 --> 01:10:32,691
right after Halloween.

1033
01:10:33,984 --> 01:10:35,194
Right.

1034
01:10:36,237 --> 01:10:38,489
-Are they testing the lights?
-Yes.

1035
01:10:38,572 --> 01:10:41,492
The Installation and Marketing Teams
have been busy today.

1036
01:11:09,061 --> 01:11:10,646
Am I hallucinating

1037
01:11:12,064 --> 01:11:13,816
the snow?

1038
01:11:13,899 --> 01:11:15,109
I see it too.

1039
01:11:16,443 --> 01:11:19,488
But isn't this just a rehearsal?

1040
01:11:19,571 --> 01:11:20,656
One minute.

1041
01:12:21,342 --> 01:12:23,927
It's snowing in the fall.

1042
01:12:25,721 --> 01:12:27,181
You wanted to see snow sooner.

1043
01:12:28,265 --> 01:12:29,767
Your wish came true.

1044
01:12:30,476 --> 01:12:31,477
You're right.

1045
01:12:32,269 --> 01:12:34,938
Things are looking up.
All my wishes are coming true.

1046
01:12:36,357 --> 01:12:39,401
I think my first love will come true too.

1047
01:12:42,071 --> 01:12:42,905
Well…

1048
01:12:44,406 --> 01:12:46,575
I don't think
that's what this snow is for.

1049
01:12:46,658 --> 01:12:47,826
Why not?

1050
01:12:48,494 --> 01:12:49,870
I bet it'll come true.

1051
01:12:50,704 --> 01:12:52,581
Who the hell is he

1052
01:12:53,332 --> 01:12:55,751
that you're so hell-bent on it?

1053
01:12:59,088 --> 01:13:03,133
I wasn't ever going to tell you

1054
01:13:03,217 --> 01:13:05,219
in case you'd become too arrogant.

1055
01:13:05,302 --> 01:13:07,137
But here's my second secret.

1056
01:13:09,098 --> 01:13:11,308
-What is it?
-Was it bus number 372?

1057
01:13:11,392 --> 01:13:13,394
-What do you mean?
-The bus you took

1058
01:13:14,019 --> 01:13:15,604
back home after work.

1059
01:13:18,565 --> 01:13:19,733
Right. Yes.

1060
01:13:19,817 --> 01:13:20,943
You're right.

1061
01:13:21,026 --> 01:13:23,529
And you always sat
in the back next to the window.

1062
01:13:24,446 --> 01:13:26,907
Yes, I did. How did you know that?

1063
01:13:26,990 --> 01:13:28,242
How do you think I know?

1064
01:13:35,374 --> 01:13:37,668
I followed your bus home

1065
01:13:37,751 --> 01:13:40,421
and crossed the Han River numerous times

1066
01:13:41,171 --> 01:13:44,466
despite all the traffic.
It took 1.5 hours.

1067
01:13:45,884 --> 01:13:46,885
Why?

1068
01:13:56,228 --> 01:14:00,524
That bus I told you about
was bus number 372.

1069
01:14:01,150 --> 01:14:02,192
And the guy is you.

1070
01:14:03,485 --> 01:14:04,319
Okay.

1071
01:14:06,989 --> 01:14:08,407
How did you even get into SNU?

1072
01:14:14,121 --> 01:14:15,122
What?

1073
01:14:15,205 --> 01:14:16,039
So it's me?

1074
01:14:17,833 --> 01:14:20,002
Me? I was the guy on the bus?

1075
01:14:20,085 --> 01:14:21,128
Yes, it was you.

1076
01:14:21,712 --> 01:14:23,630
How lovey-dovey.

1077
01:14:23,714 --> 01:14:27,176
By the way, why did
the Installation Team sprinkle snow?

1078
01:14:27,259 --> 01:14:28,969
It was Director Baek's request.

1079
01:14:29,052 --> 01:14:32,556
Sir, please test the snowmaker
during the rehearsal.

1080
01:14:33,140 --> 01:14:36,727
I don't think that's necessary.

1081
01:14:37,227 --> 01:14:40,647
The Legal Team
needs to prepare themselves.

1082
01:14:40,731 --> 01:14:42,983
You know it'd be an issue
if a customer slipped and fell.

1083
01:14:43,066 --> 01:14:46,695
I need to determine
how slippery it'll get.

1084
01:14:47,446 --> 01:14:49,156
Sure, if you must.

1085
01:14:49,239 --> 01:14:51,992
I'd like big snowflakes if possible.

1086
01:14:52,075 --> 01:14:54,036
All right then.

1087
01:14:54,119 --> 01:14:55,621
-Thank you, sir.
-No problem.

1088
01:14:57,539 --> 01:15:00,959
I sense love in the air.

1089
01:15:01,043 --> 01:15:01,960
Right?

1090
01:15:02,044 --> 01:15:04,213
Divorce then remarriage.

1091
01:15:05,839 --> 01:15:06,840
It's possible?

1092
01:15:06,924 --> 01:15:08,342
Was it really me?

1093
01:15:09,134 --> 01:15:10,844
Was I your first love?

1094
01:15:15,265 --> 01:15:16,433
They must've left already.

1095
01:15:16,517 --> 01:15:18,227
I wonder when they'll arrive.

1096
01:15:23,815 --> 01:15:25,817
It'll take some time.

1097
01:15:25,901 --> 01:15:27,903
My morning prayers were answered.

1098
01:15:28,570 --> 01:15:31,990
Hae-in will get better after the surgery

1099
01:15:32,866 --> 01:15:34,660
and be happy with Hyun-woo.

1100
01:15:36,245 --> 01:15:37,329
You see…

1101
01:15:39,831 --> 01:15:40,874
There's a problem.

1102
01:15:42,751 --> 01:15:43,585
What problem?

1103
01:15:43,669 --> 01:15:45,587
After receiving surgery…

1104
01:15:47,214 --> 01:15:48,048
Oh, dear.

1105
01:15:49,132 --> 01:15:51,718
She might lose her memory.

1106
01:15:53,637 --> 01:15:54,972
What do you mean?

1107
01:15:55,889 --> 01:15:58,058
That could be a side effect.

1108
01:15:58,809 --> 01:16:00,269
But what choice do we have?

1109
01:16:00,811 --> 01:16:01,895
She needs to live.

1110
01:16:18,328 --> 01:16:20,080
We had no choice.

1111
01:16:20,163 --> 01:16:23,875
I asked Hyun-woo to keep it a secret.

1112
01:16:27,212 --> 01:16:28,046
That was…

1113
01:16:30,215 --> 01:16:31,466
wise of you.

1114
01:16:32,968 --> 01:16:36,096
She has a terrible personality
since she takes after me.

1115
01:16:37,014 --> 01:16:39,308
So she might've refused
to get the surgery.

1116
01:16:39,933 --> 01:16:40,767
But…

1117
01:16:41,935 --> 01:16:42,978
Still…

1118
01:16:44,730 --> 01:16:46,732
What'll we do about our poor baby?

1119
01:17:00,537 --> 01:17:02,998
Poor baby…

1120
01:17:20,766 --> 01:17:21,850
Are you okay?

1121
01:17:24,019 --> 01:17:25,437
Of course I am.

1122
01:17:26,563 --> 01:17:27,439
Don't worry.

1123
01:17:50,712 --> 01:17:52,547
Are you going to Frankfurt?

1124
01:17:53,048 --> 01:17:54,049
Yes.

1125
01:18:00,430 --> 01:18:05,602
BODY FOUND NEAR SAMBANG RESERVOIR
IDENTIFIED AS LAND BROKER, MR. PYEON

1126
01:18:35,465 --> 01:18:36,675
What's the third one?

1127
01:18:38,093 --> 01:18:39,094
What do you mean?

1128
01:18:39,970 --> 01:18:42,889
You had three secrets
to tell me before the surgery.

1129
01:18:43,640 --> 01:18:45,058
You only told me two so far.

1130
01:18:45,142 --> 01:18:46,309
Oh, that?

1131
01:18:50,188 --> 01:18:51,106
The third one is…

1132
01:18:53,442 --> 01:18:55,277
-Yeong-suk.
-Yeong-suk?

1133
01:18:56,153 --> 01:18:58,071
-The raccoon on the rooftop?
-Yes.

1134
01:19:01,283 --> 01:19:03,118
I never got to see her.

1135
01:19:03,201 --> 01:19:04,161
Seriously.

1136
01:19:04,244 --> 01:19:05,704
Not even once.

1137
01:19:06,955 --> 01:19:08,832
-What about her?
-I made it up.

1138
01:19:14,671 --> 01:19:17,591
How could a raccoon live there?
Did you really believe that?

1139
01:19:21,636 --> 01:19:22,971
Gosh.

1140
01:19:24,639 --> 01:19:26,308
You duped me for four years.

1141
01:19:27,601 --> 01:19:29,853
I called out her name
every time I was up there.

1142
01:19:30,479 --> 01:19:31,438
You fool.

1143
01:19:57,339 --> 01:19:58,423
Is this it?

1144
01:20:00,634 --> 01:20:01,510
Hae-in.

1145
01:20:02,511 --> 01:20:03,512
What is it?

1146
01:20:04,554 --> 01:20:05,388
There's something

1147
01:20:06,223 --> 01:20:08,141
I didn't tell you as well.

1148
01:20:08,809 --> 01:20:09,643
What is it?

1149
01:20:15,482 --> 01:20:16,525
Tell me.

1150
01:20:17,442 --> 01:20:18,902
Is something wrong?

1151
01:20:22,072 --> 01:20:23,448
Can they not operate

1152
01:20:23,949 --> 01:20:25,242
on me?

1153
01:20:26,993 --> 01:20:27,953
No, that's not it.

1154
01:20:32,123 --> 01:20:32,958
It's…

1155
01:20:34,501 --> 01:20:35,335
highly likely

1156
01:20:37,128 --> 01:20:41,299
that you'll lose your memory
after the surgery.

1157
01:20:42,551 --> 01:20:43,552
What do you mean?

1158
01:20:45,428 --> 01:20:46,263
What memory?

1159
01:20:48,723 --> 01:20:49,558
Probably…

1160
01:20:50,851 --> 01:20:51,935
all of it.

1161
01:20:53,270 --> 01:20:54,771
You'll forget

1162
01:20:54,855 --> 01:20:58,817
everyone, the places you've been,

1163
01:21:00,569 --> 01:21:02,320
and all the experiences you've had.

1164
01:21:11,204 --> 01:21:13,832
Even still, this is

1165
01:21:14,875 --> 01:21:16,376
your only chance

1166
01:21:16,459 --> 01:21:18,044
to live.

1167
01:21:25,802 --> 01:21:27,012
So…

1168
01:21:28,930 --> 01:21:29,973
you're telling me

1169
01:21:32,225 --> 01:21:33,602
to make a decision?

1170
01:21:35,812 --> 01:21:39,357
I'll lose my memory if I get it
and die if I don't.

1171
01:21:40,150 --> 01:21:42,360
Are you telling me
to pick the lesser evil?

1172
01:21:45,071 --> 01:21:45,906
No.

1173
01:21:45,989 --> 01:21:47,115
Then what?

1174
01:21:49,242 --> 01:21:50,243
Forget it.

1175
01:21:52,787 --> 01:21:54,998
I'll pretend like
this was all a good dream.

1176
01:22:11,598 --> 01:22:13,308
Let me go. I said, let go.

1177
01:22:15,310 --> 01:22:16,478
Don't make a choice.

1178
01:22:17,479 --> 01:22:18,730
Don't think.

1179
01:22:20,231 --> 01:22:21,274
Just listen to me.

1180
01:22:22,609 --> 01:22:25,153
Just… live.

1181
01:22:28,114 --> 01:22:29,074
Do that.

1182
01:22:31,117 --> 01:22:32,202
Please…

1183
01:22:33,286 --> 01:22:34,120
live.

1184
01:22:35,914 --> 01:22:36,790
Okay?

1185
01:23:43,690 --> 01:23:45,066
Hi, Hae-in.

1186
01:23:47,652 --> 01:23:50,739
I'm Baek Hyun-woo.

1187
01:23:53,033 --> 01:23:56,494
I'm your husband.

1188
01:23:57,203 --> 01:24:00,206
You must be confused and scared.

1189
01:24:00,290 --> 01:24:01,207
Me too.

1190
01:24:01,791 --> 01:24:03,334
You don't remember anything

1191
01:24:03,418 --> 01:24:05,503
and a stranger
is claiming to be your husband.

1192
01:24:05,587 --> 01:24:06,921
You must be so confused.

1193
01:24:19,809 --> 01:24:20,935
But…

1194
01:24:22,353 --> 01:24:23,480
this is good news.

1195
01:24:24,147 --> 01:24:25,273
You…

1196
01:24:25,356 --> 01:24:27,150
You were very sick,

1197
01:24:27,233 --> 01:24:28,693
but you're better now.

1198
01:24:33,907 --> 01:24:36,993
You must be curious
about what kind of person you used to be.

1199
01:24:39,204 --> 01:24:40,413
It must be upsetting

1200
01:24:41,539 --> 01:24:42,749
that you can't remember.

1201
01:24:45,085 --> 01:24:46,211
But don't worry.

1202
01:24:47,754 --> 01:24:48,797
Because I…

1203
01:24:51,508 --> 01:24:53,051
I remember everything.

1204
01:24:54,969 --> 01:24:56,387
I'll tell you everything…

1205
01:24:59,099 --> 01:25:00,308
that I know.

1206
01:25:05,021 --> 01:25:06,731
I shouldn't cry.

1207
01:25:09,400 --> 01:25:11,945
This will be the first time

1208
01:25:13,071 --> 01:25:14,614
you see my face.

1209
01:25:20,662 --> 01:25:22,038
And let me warn you.

1210
01:25:23,540 --> 01:25:27,627
Even if I'm not your ideal type,

1211
01:25:27,710 --> 01:25:31,005
I'm sorry, but I can't break up with you.

1212
01:25:31,923 --> 01:25:32,924
Because we agreed

1213
01:25:34,592 --> 01:25:36,928
not to part ways just because

1214
01:25:37,554 --> 01:25:38,763
of a change of mind.

1215
01:25:39,889 --> 01:25:41,516
Even if you don't like me…

1216
01:25:43,726 --> 01:25:45,019
No matter what happens…

1217
01:25:46,771 --> 01:25:47,605
Even if…

1218
01:25:52,944 --> 01:25:54,320
you forget

1219
01:25:55,655 --> 01:25:56,739
the promise we made,

1220
01:25:58,741 --> 01:25:59,576
I promised

1221
01:26:01,119 --> 01:26:02,412
to be…

1222
01:26:04,831 --> 01:26:06,124
by your side.

1223
01:26:11,296 --> 01:26:12,755
Let's welcome the first snow,

1224
01:26:13,423 --> 01:26:14,591
stick by each other,

1225
01:26:14,674 --> 01:26:18,094
and spend our everyday lives together.

1226
01:26:19,846 --> 01:26:21,347
Let's fill up

1227
01:26:23,224 --> 01:26:24,642
that empty candy jar

1228
01:26:26,227 --> 01:26:27,437
of yours.

1229
01:26:31,024 --> 01:26:32,066
We can do it.

1230
01:26:32,775 --> 01:26:35,570
Because it was fate
that brought us together.

1231
01:26:40,450 --> 01:26:41,659
I love…

1232
01:26:46,080 --> 01:26:47,373
I love you, Hae-in.

1233
01:26:50,752 --> 01:26:51,878
I've always loved you…

1234
01:26:55,423 --> 01:26:56,841
and will continue to do so.

1235
01:27:04,849 --> 01:27:07,685
QUEEN OF TEARS

1236
01:27:38,591 --> 01:27:39,884
I still remember

1237
01:27:39,968 --> 01:27:41,761
the smell,

1238
01:27:41,844 --> 01:27:43,805
the moon, and the wind of that day.

1239
01:27:43,888 --> 01:27:45,723
Don't pray

1240
01:27:45,807 --> 01:27:47,100
about dying.

1241
01:27:47,183 --> 01:27:49,602
That so-called family of yours
will get hurt.

1242
01:27:50,144 --> 01:27:51,604
Da-hye…

1243
01:27:51,688 --> 01:27:53,189
I lived as myself,

1244
01:27:53,731 --> 01:27:54,607
and I'll die as such

1245
01:27:55,191 --> 01:27:56,234
I won't let that happen.

1246
01:27:56,317 --> 01:27:59,279
That's how he found that hospital.

1247
01:27:59,362 --> 01:28:00,363
I'll help you.

1248
01:28:00,446 --> 01:28:02,198
Don't do this to me.

1249
01:28:02,282 --> 01:28:04,826
Don't make me want to live.

1250
01:28:06,077 --> 01:28:06,995
Hae-in!

1251
01:28:12,041 --> 01:28:14,043
Subtitle translation by Soo-ji Kim
